    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The warning message only shows when the old implementation would have triggered a sort, i.e. when the non-concatenation axis is not already aligned. The warning message and the whatsnew should all be read in that context.\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/21101 for an issue with the warning message.\r\n\r\nThe old behavior of sorting if and only if the non-concatenation axis is not already aligned isn't very useful IMO. Do you have a use case where it was useful?"
